content:
Meet Steve Jacobowitz, the longest serving photographer at ABC7NY. He's been with us since 1966!

Today he covered the completion of the new Kosciusko Bridge. 

And remarked that the last time NY opened a bridge (the Verrazano-Narrows), he was there too! 

(Of course that was two years before he joined ABC. He was 17 then and working as a short order cook, catering the event. Which makes this story even cooler.)

content:
By now you've probably seen Jimmy Kimmel's gut-wrenching recounting of his newborn son's heart condition.

His monologue could not have come at a better time for Democrats in Congress, who have been fighting to protect Obamacare from the latest GOP effort to repeal it.

Today a key Republican pulled his support, saying the new bill would "torpedo" protections for people with preexisting conditions like what Kimmel's son will live with for the rest of his life.
name: Josh Einiger
title: Jimmy Kimmel’s Emotional Monologue: His New Son’s Heart Condition

content:
It's hard to believe it's been two years since the city wept.

25 year old NYPD Officer Brian Moore was shot in the face two years ago tonight, after he was shot point-blank in the face while on an anti-crime patrol in Queens Village.

Nearly 2 million people saw this heartbreaking video I posted two days later, when the NYPD ambulance carried his flag-draped casket out of Jamaica Hospital, after his family decided to take him off life support.

Our first responders have had an awful time these past few years - members of the NYPD, the New York City Fire Department (FDNY) and FDNY EMS have all died in the line of duty.

Next time you see a first responder, make sure you say thank you.
name: Josh Einiger

content:
NYC may be the biggest magnet for terrorists in the world.  But in NYC, it might surprise you to learn some of the biggest targets are not the responsibility of the NYPD. 

Instead, it's the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey Police Department that secures our airports, the WTC, the bus terminal and our busiest bridges and tunnels.

We had a rare and exclusive look inside the PAPD's elite special ops unit, as they trained for the worst. On Channel 7 at 5, and later on ABC7NY.
name: Josh Einiger
